CRT Capital Group LLC, the
institutional brokerage firm backed by Aquiline Capital
Partners, hired Matthew DeSalvo as chief operating officer.  DeSalvo, 54, former head of stock sales and trading for
Zurich-based Credit Suisse Group AG, earlier worked at Morgan
Stanley, Stamford, Connecticut-based CRT said today in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
